By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has informed that three new associations have applied to be registered as political parties after conclusion of the 2019 general elections. This goes to show that the number of political parties in the country will soon jump to over 100. This is apart from the 11 undergoing processing before suspension of party registration ahead of the 2019 polls. Recall that the Independent National Electoral Commission yesterday complained that that multiple political parties that took part in the February general election created logistics problems. Details shortly… 